I did a CTRL-C while conda was updating itself at just the wrong time. The result was the removal of conda.  I can't find an especially good way to get it back.  In the end I had to reinstall Anaconda from scratch.  I only after realized that a pip install _may_ have worked.  Maybe putting a signal handler to catch CTRL-C would be a good idea so conda installs don't leave things in an inconsistent state.

